__init__(string,address,string,string).details: To omit the opcodes for checking the `msg.value` in the creation-time EVM bytecode, the constructor is declared as `payable`.

params.base_uri_: The maximum 80-character user-readable string base URI for computing `voterURI`.
params.name_eip712_: The maximum 50-character user-readable string name of the signing domain, i.e. the name of the dApp or protocol.
params.token_: The address of the ERC20 smart-contract that manages voting.
params.version_eip712_: The maximum 20-character current main version of the signing domain. Signatures from different versions are not compatible.

add_nominee(address,string).details: Safely registers `nominee` and adds it to `nominees`.

hasVoted(address).details: Returns if the user has voted or not.

isRegistred(address).details: Returns if the user is registred or not.

renounce_ownership().details: Leaves the contract without an owner.

safe_register(address,string).details: Safely registers `voter_id` and assigns it to a `owner`.

params.uri: The maximum 432-character user-readable string URI for computing `voterURI`.

totalVoters().details: Returns the amount of voters in existence.

transfer_ownership(address).details: Transfers the ownership of the contract to a new account `new_owner`.

params.new_owner: The 20-byte address of the new owner.

params.for_: The addresss of the nominee the voter is voting for.

voterURI(uint256).details: Returns the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for the `voter_id` voter.

returns._0: String The maximum 512-character user-readable string voter URI of the `voter_id` voter.

__init__(string,address,string,string).notice: The `owner` role will be assigned to the `msg.sender`.

add_nominee(address,string).notice: Only the owner can access this function. Note that `owner` cannot be the zero address. Also, new voters will be automatically assigned an incremental ID.

renounce_ownership().notice: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transfer_ownership(address).notice: Note that thisa function can only be called by the current `owner`. Also, the `new_owner` cannot be the zero address.
